&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title and Grade:&lt;/strong&gt; A&amp;E Nurse, Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location/Trust:&lt;/strong&gt; Worcestershire Acute Trust, Worcester Royal Hospital &amp; Alexandra Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wards Covered:&lt;/strong&gt; A&amp;E&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Rates: &lt;/strong&gt;Days: £15.66 Saturdays/Nights: £20.35 Sunday/Bank Hols: £25.05&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Winter Incentive Now Available (Only available for shifts worked at Worcester Acute NHS Trust)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to work in an environment where there is a real supportive and inclusive ethos and sense of community? Would you like to work as a team where all team members are compassionate and committed to delivering high standard care and services to patients? Would you like your work to be flexible to fit your lifestyle and circumstances? Would you like to have the flexibility of working in different locations, giving you the opportunity to expand your experience and knowledge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you answered ‘yes’ to the above, we’d love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have flexible Bank shifts available for A&amp;E Nurses available at Worcestershire Acute Trust specifically in the following wards and areas: in A&amp;E/AEC departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills/Responsibilities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this post, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have a minimum of 6 months paid experience at Band 5 level as an A&amp;E Registered Nurse in a hospital environment within the last 2 years&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comply with NMC Professional Registration and keep up to date with current nursing practices&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Undertake nursing assessment and evaluation to enable development of appropriate plans of care based on the needs of the individual&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be proficient in the delivery of care to patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure safe administration of drugs in accordance with NMC and CHS policies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ensure accurate records are kept in accordance with CHS policy and NMC guidelines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carry out nursing procedures and techniques in accordance with agreed policies and standards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Undertake regular mandatory training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Register today for various flexible shifts and long term placement opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information on the roles or details on how to join NHS Professionals, simply get in touch with the team by calling07423 669079 or email Natalie.Peace@nhsprofessionals.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you soon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Disclaimer &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note, you will be contacted by email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your emails, including your junk/spam regularly. We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
